programme.title: Rebel Without a Cause
programme.desc: Inarticulate teenage alienation, rebelliousness and torment break out in violence in this character study about a sullen youth (James Dean) who moves with his parents to a well-to-do Los Angeles suburb, where he finds love, friendship and new enemies. (Repeat).

programme.title: East of Eden
programme.desc: An adaptation of John Steinbeck's 1955 novel is set in 1917 California, and stars James Dean as a wild and unloved young man from a strife-torn family who is at odds with his quiet, studious brother and puritanical father. Jo Van Fleet won a Supporting Actress Oscar as the boys' estranged mother. (Repeat).

programme.title: Picnic
programme.desc: Best Picture nominee is an adaptation of William Inge's Pulitzer-winning play about a handsome drifter who ambles into a small Kansas town during the Labor Day weekend and causes a ruckus among some of the female population. (Repeat).

programme.title: High Wall
programme.desc: A World War II veteran suffering from a recurring brain injury teams with a woman psychiatrist to prove himself innocent of his wife's murder. (Repeat).

programme.title: Side Street
programme.desc: Overwhelmed by the pressure to provide for his young family, a man steals money from a shady lawyer's office—which lands him into deeper trouble than expected. (Repeat).

programme.title: Fallen Angel
programme.desc: A shady drifter tries to take a small-town woman for her money. Complications: a waitress and murder. Often absorbing Otto Preminger film, despite some dramatic lapses. Well acted. (Repeat).

programme.title: He Walked by Night
programme.desc: Fact-based suspenser about a psychopathic burglar who keeps the police off-balance by varying his MO...until he kills a cop. (Repeat).

programme.title: Titanic
programme.desc: Vivid re-creation of the sinking of the 1912 luxury liner, tied to a plausible fictional story of its passengers. Technically quite impressive. Clifton Webb, Barbara Stanwyck, Robert Wagner, Audrey Dalton, Brian Aherne. Jean Negulesco directed. (Repeat).

programme.title: Dangerous Passage
programme.desc: Attempted sabotage on a boat. Joe: Robert Lowery. Nita: Phyllis Brooks. Bergstrom: Charles Arnt. Directed by William Berke. (Repeat).

programme.title: Stowaway
programme.desc: Shirley Temple sings, dances and dispenses charm from Shanghai to the U.S. as a waif who falls asleep in a playboy's car that winds up on a cruise ship headed for the States. After being discovered at sea, she plays Cupid for the playboy and the fellow passenger he falls for. (Repeat).

programme.title: Happy Land
programme.desc: An Iowa family must cope with the loss of a son in World War II. Moving, effective tearjerker. (Repeat).

programme.title: Monkey Business
programme.desc: A chemist attempting to find a rejuvenation formula in his lab is tricked when a concoction accidentally mixed by a test monkey winds up in the water cooler. (Repeat).

programme.title: Arsenic and Old Lace
programme.desc: Macabre comedy about a pair of sweet old ladies from Brooklyn who put lonely bachelors out of their misery with sips from their arsenic-laced elderberry wine---"acts of mercy" that their visiting nephew finds hard to swallow. The film is based on Joseph Kesselring's Broadway play, a long-running hit that contractually delayed release of the picture almost three years (Repeat).

programme.title: His Girl Friday
programme.desc: Rewrite of the Ben Hecht-Charles MacArthur play "The Front Page" is about a newspaper editor who goes to extraordinary lengths to keep his best reporter (who is also his ex-wife) from remarrying in a desperate attempt to win her back. (Repeat).

programme.title: I Was a Male War Bride
programme.desc: French Captain Henri Rochard and American Lieutenant Catherine Gates fall in love while working on a mission in post WWII Germany. They marry but are pulled apart when Catherine is called back to the U.S.A., so they invoke the War Brides Act which allows the spouse of American army personnel to enter the country. (Repeat).

programme.title: An Affair to Remember
programme.desc: A man and woman meet and fall in love while aboard an ocean liner en route to New York. They agree to meet at the top of the Empire State building in six months to resume their romance provided they've both ended their current respective relationships. Remake of the 1939 classic "Love Affair." (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Charade

programme.title: In Love and War
programme.desc: Adaptation of Anton Myrer's "The Big War," a portrait of WWII's impact on three Marines. Robert Wagner, Jeffrey Hunter, Bradford Dillman, Dana Wynter, Hope Lange, Sheree North, Mort Sahl. Directed by Philip Dunne. (Repeat).(n)
